---------------------------------------------------------
 if Statement ( If then , If then else, If elif else)
---------------------------------------------------------
Note: string/integer attach to a variable
{srting variable  like- word=abc }
{integer variable like- cont=10  }
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Integer: a whole number, such as 3 0r 4, but not 3.4 or 4.8
string: string is any serise of characters like- "hello" or "LKH197".
--------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------
Integer comparision:
--------------------
-eg - is equal to -      if ["$a" -eq "$b"]
-ne - is not equal to    if ["$a" -ne "$b"]
-gt - is grater than -             if ["$a" -gt "$b"]
-ge - is grater than or equal to   if ["$a" -ge "$b"]
-lt - is less tha                  if ["$a" -lt "$b"]
-le - is less than or equal to     if ["$a" -le "$b"]

<  -   is less than -                (("$a" < "$b"))
<= -   is less than 0r equal to -    (("$a" <= "$b"))
>  -   is grater than -              (("$a" > ""$b))
>= -   is grater than or equal to -  (("$a" >= "$b"))

note: use single square brakets.[], when Use comparision oprater with integers comparisions
then
note: use dubble pranthesess (()), when Use angels brakets on integers comparisions
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------
String comparision
------------------
=  - is equal to if ["$a" = "$b"]
== - is equal to if ["$a" == "$b"]
!= - is not equal to ["$a" != "$b"]

< - is less than, in ASCII alphabetical order - if [["$a" < "$b"]]
> - is grater than, in ASCII alphabetical order - if [["$a" > "$b"]]
-z - string is null than is has zero length
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Integer comparision:

#! /bin/bash

 count=10  #declare a variable
 
 if [ $count -eq 9 ]
 then
   echo "condition is true"
 fi
 save
 
ubuntu@ubuntu-VPCEA35FG:~/Desktop$ ./hello.sh 
